    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-14T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-14T23:00:00-05:00" n="519"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d519">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/418: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-15T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 15, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received September 15—9:35
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>813. May I inform the Japanese and other interested Legations of the substance of
                    the Department’s 317, September 12, 8 p.m.?<note n="66" xml:id="d519fn66">Not
                        printed; it quoted the text of the memorandum of September 12, 1930, to the
                        Chinese Legation, <ref target="#pg_467">p. 467</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
